  I managed to get my second Manticore Mane last night and now only need the 2 Sire Hairs to finish the 6th shawl.  Please impart your knowledge on how to hunt these bad ladies.  I know they are in Cobalt Scar and are underwater... but I know really nothing else.<br>
<br>
Everything else in this quest has been soloable (is that a word?) - although I did get exp from two Manticore's lol.  I imagine the Siren's are the hardest part, so I am wondering if I can do this solo or not.<br>
<br>
What level are they around?<br>
Where is a good spot to hunt them?<br>
Do they wander or are they static spawns?<br>
I hear they are enchanters... is that true?<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance for your help.  Depending on your answers I may need some help this weekend taking a couple locks of hair from these wenches. =) <p><p align="center"><strong><font size="2" face="Arial">Mullzy &lt;Infinitus Vindicat&gt; ~
Shaman 55</font><br>
</strong><img src="http://www.telusplanet.net/public/rmulzet/eq/mullet.jpg" width="315"
height="14"> </p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/umoonie1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>moonie1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/24/01 3:20:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 6th Shawl - Siren Hair info please!</span><hr size=1> The siren hairs are a pain.  They drop off the enticers. I wouldn't dare try to solo them.  Jaharad and I hunted them in cs at the sg zone.  He would try to pull them at the tunnel entrance but the pathing sucks. I had to assist and nuke most of the time before they would come. They also charm.  Between the sirens nuking me and a charmed monkey beating the crap out of me it was very bad for my health.  I had to zone a lot to stay alive. You also get a few enchantresses which were blue to me at 57.  I would take friends and make sure your mr is high.  You still get charmed with the high mr but it doesn't seem to last has long.  Also if you get a runed sea shell keep it. It's for the 7th shawl. The hairs are no drop but the runed sea shell is not.  Hope that helps.  If you have anymore questions just send me a tell. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/umullzy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mullzy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Councilman</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/24/01 3:26:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 6th Shawl - Siren Hair info please!</span><hr size=1> Thanks Moonie.  Aye... I bet a 60 monk beating on you isn't a lot of fun. =)<br>
<br>
I have zoned into SG a couple times and just below the enterance I remember seeing a couple in the water.  Are those the spawns you pulled? Or do you have to go for a swim? =)<br>
<br>
Thanks for your help. <p><p align="center"><strong><font size="2" face="Arial">Mullzy &lt;Infinitus Vindicat&gt; ~
Shaman 55</font><br>
</strong><img src="http://www.telusplanet.net/public/rmulzet/eq/mullet.jpg" width="315"
height="14"> </p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/uginweil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ginweil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/24/01 4:40:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 6th Shawl - Siren Hair info please!</span><hr size=1> ROFL! I was in CS trying to find Rywen's corpse underwater once, and one of these sirens charmed me. She sent me all the way up the cliff, and I proceeded to 86 this poor necro's pet. LOL, when I finally got control of myself, I heard in /shout<br>
&quot;WTF is this Ginweil that just got trained on me!?! Someone come kill this please!&quot;<br>
I couldn't stop laughing.....the guy freaked when I sent him a tell explaining it....he thought I was a pissed off NPC. <p>Ginweil Splitfeather
55 Outrider - Infinitus Vindicat<BR>
<img src="http://home.wi.rr.com/ginweil/GinSig.jpg">
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/umoonie1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>moonie1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/24/01 5:32:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 6th Shawl - Siren Hair info please!</span><hr size=1> He was just pulling the 2 spawns at the end of the tunnel most of the time.  Sometimes there was a roamer that came close to the tunnel.  I can't remember the spawn time but I had enough time to med to full between pulls.  It will probably take you a few hours to get the hairs though.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/uwalkerbohh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Walker Bohh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/25/01 7:56:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 6th Shawl - Siren Hair info please!</span><hr size=1> Mullzy check out this link please. The information you seek is about 3/4 of the way down the page--- How to pull...<br>
