<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm18.showMessage?topicID=52.topic">pub13.ezboard.com/fthedru...D=52.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p><img src=http://www.mdvl.net/~toes/walker2.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ugavick.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gavick</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/25/01 11:00:51 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 6th Shawl - Siren Hair info please!</span><hr size=1> Mullzy I have some info that may help you out.<br>
<br>
1. They don't see invis. So you can scout em out without any difficulty.<br>
<br>
2.  Root em and dot em.  You should be able to do this from outside of their casting range.  Just make sure where you are sitting isn't within the agro range of another siren.  Now the obvious problem for you is that you can't snare them.  So when root breaks they will get in casting range quickly.  Perhaps hunting them with a druid doing the quests would be a good idea (I am on the 4th atm), your druid can snare, eb you both and help with dots.<br>
<br>
I have not done the root dot technique myself but have read on boards that is a good way for druids to solo the sirens.  As soon as it is rooted, back away a bit and dot it.  The trick is to be at the maximum casting range for your dot.  This will give you the biggest cushion.  So try casting a few times when you are out of range and move slowly closer until you can cast.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps, and if you want to camp em with me, feel free to give me a shout either here or on the SOF boards, or in game.  I could always bank a couple of Siren Hairs, and there would still be xp coming in.<br>
